In [62]: 
λlist = 0:0.1:2.5

    λ = λlist[i]
    βhatSVM[:, i] = svm(ctr, Xtr, λ, 1)
    errSVM[i] = 1.0 - sum(cte .== sign(Xte * βhatSVM[:, i])) / length(cte)
end

run(`cat hw4.jl`)

#
# This function fits lp regression with responses y and design matrix X
# possibly with Lasso penalty
#
function lpreg(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64},
               p::Float64, λ::Float64=0.0)

  # Create optimization variables
  βhat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(norm(y - X * βhat, p) + λ * norm(βhat[2:end], 1))
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  βhat.value

end

#
# This function fits τ-quantile regression with responses y and design matrix X
# possibily with Lasso penalty
#
function quantreg(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64},
                  τ::Float64, λ::Float64=0.0)

  # Create optimization variables
  βhat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  res = Variable(size(X, 1))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(sum(τ * pos(res) - (1.0 - τ) * neg(res)) +
                     λ * sum(abs(βhat[2:end])))
  problem.constraints += y - X * βhat == res
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  βhat.value

end

#
# This function computes Dantzig selector solution with responses y
# and design matrix X
#
function dantzig(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64}, λ::Float64=0.0)

  # Create optimization variables
  βhat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(norm(X' * (y - X * βhat), Inf))
  problem.constraints += sum(abs(βhat[2:end])) <= λ
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  βhat.value

end

#
# This function computes SVM solution with responses y
# and design matrix X
#
function svm(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64}, λ::Float64, p::Int=1)

  # Create optimization variables
  βhat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(sum(pos(1.0 - y .* (X * βhat))))
  problem.constraints += norm(βhat[2:end], p) <= λ
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  βhat.value

end
